abstract: GoPro is only one of nearly 20 companies looking to make their market debuts this week, a pace unseen since the height of the dot-com boom in 2000.
snippet: GoPro is only one of nearly 20 companies looking to make their market debuts this week, a pace unseen since the height of the dot-com boom in 2000.
lead_paragraph: Updated, 7:19 p.m. | Since its founding in 2004, GoPro has become the biggest name in action videos, its tiny cameras attached to hundreds of surfboards, sports bikes and skydiving helmets.

headline.main: GoPro’s I.P.O. Prices at Top of Range, Leading a Wave of Newly Public Companies
headline.print_headline: GoPro’s I.P.O. Prices at Top of Range, Leading a Wave of Newly Public Companies

byline.original: By Michael J. de la Merced
